<br>
- I disagree, keep it the way it is now.  All this does is discourage pvp in general and make people leave the server.  I'd rather see them add a reward for pking so that people want to pk, instead of wanting to avoid pvp.<br>
<br>
#2 - Naked pvp kill corpses do not poof upon looting.<br>
<br>
I disagree here too, this is the number one rule in place to stop bind rushing type tactics.  It makes it a real penalty to bind in enemy territory, or anywhere not safe for that matter.  <br>
<br>
<br>
#3 - Merge Good and Newt teams OR allow evils to pk each other for points/insignias<br>
<br>
I don't know if I like either of these solutions, evils are the hardest team to pk with thats for sure, its very hard to find even targets for the high lvl evils, but I think as neutrals/goods level up this won't be as much of a factor.<br>
<br>
#4 - No negative points for pvp kills, only positive based on the current system of 100-5*level difference up to 20levels lower.<br>
<br>
I agree with this change, with negative points for killing low lvls it takes away all meaning to the point system for me.<br>
<br>
#5 - HOW ABOUT ADDING SOME GOD DAMN PLACE FOR EVILS TO TURN IN INSIGNIAS?<br>
<br>
True for all teams, this is the biggest disapointment of the server for me, reward for pvp would be a nice way to encourage it.<br>
<br>
#6 - Exp loss for pvp death ONLY if killer/victim is even, no more exp loss when killed by a green<br>
<br>
I agree with this somewhat, with a 5 lvl range for even cons its grossly unfair that greens make you lose exp.  2 lvl 50's should and will be able to kill a lvl 56 in a fair fight, as it is the 56 more or less has to run because he's at risk and they aren't.  I also think people should be even con to a greater level, maybe +/- 10.<br>
<br>
#7 - Item Loot for pvp kills - allow looting of 1 item, whether no-drop or not, possibly limit to the most common jewelery spots: Ears, Neck, Face, Head, Fingers, Wrists.<br>
<br>
Disagree, Rallos Zek is the bluest pvp server for a reason.  Item loot leads to low quality naked/no drop pvp and people avoiding pvp.  I have never seen a server with a bluer mentality(outside the pk guilds)  than RZ.<br>
<br>
#8 - Eliminate the PvP 1.5x debuff factor, instead, limit Resists to a PvP Maximum of 100-125 no matter what. This 150-250 pvp resists is just stupid for high end pvp.<br>
<br>
If anything they should double the debuff factor.  I agree that resists are out of hand, but I don't think they should cap them.  They should maybe make 150 the magic number for resisting all magic based spells and make snare effects break over time the way root does.  They also should nerf 'non-resistable' dot's, but thats not going to happen.<br>
<br>
#9 - Meaningful rewards for turning in Superior Insignias<br>
<br>
of course<br>
<br>
#10 - Expand our bank capacity, possibly with 20-slot bank only bags. Its just not fair to make up have to destroy items to hold all the pvp coins.<br>
<br>
If they added meaningful rewards for coins this would no longer be an issue.<br>
<br>
#11 - Allow research casters an item that will hold every possible Rune/Page/item for their research, the limit of bank space due to 1 character per account is too strict.<br>
<br>
indifferent<br>
<br>
#12 - Eliminate pet targeting in PvP, this /pet target victim, and then /assist pet to find a target in a zone is just a total exploit.<br>
<br>
true, there are a lot of exploits, I'd like to see them all fixed.<br>
<br>
#13 - Titles for the top 3 pvp scorers on each team.<br>
<br>
sure, it would probably lead to people abusing the system, but it would also encourage more pvp.<br>
<br>
